            , auctioneer, Corn-street, Bristol.</p>
               <p>with intent to defraud the 
               <persName id="t18221204-71-victim626" type="victimName">
                     <rs id="t18221204-71-viclabel385" type="occupation">Governor and Company of the Bank of England</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18221204-71-victim626 t18221204-71-viclabel385"></join>
                     <interp inst="t18221204-71-victim626" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                  </persName>
             - he at the time of so uttering and publishing the same as true, well knowing the same to be forged and counterfeit against the statute.</p>
               <p>SECOND COUNT, for disposing of and putting away instead of uttering and publishing as true.</p>
               <p>TWO OTHER COUNTS, the same only stating his intent to be to defraud 
               
                  <persName id="t18221204-71-victim628" type="victimName">
                     John 
                     Cox
                  <interp inst="t18221204-71-victim628" type="surname" value="Cox"></interp>
